Description: Foundry Linux developer toolkit — desktop-agnostic
 The complete Foundry Linux developer toolkit for existing Ubuntu installs.
 Safe on any Ubuntu flavour (GNOME, XFCE, Budgie, KDE, …) — pulls in zero
 KDE or Plasma dependencies.
 .
 Includes the WorldFoundry authoring stack (Blender + 10 WF CLIs + WF
 Blender add-ons), the retro-porting toolkit (MAME, dasm, z80,
 cc65, …; Ghidra is atelier-only), light universe emulators, game-dev
 frameworks (SDL2/3, SFML, Allegro, libtcod, Tiled, LOVE + Vulkan shader
 tools), CLI image utilities, go-task, btop and dust (du-dust, an intuitive
 disk-usage viewer), and Java 17 + 21 LTS runtimes (LibGDX, Gradle, and
 mod toolchains).
 .
 On the Foundry Linux ISO, foundry-anvil (= foundry-core + foundry-desktop)
 is pre-installed instead. Existing Ubuntu users should install this package.
